# Mail compose (record context)

No global “Compose” menu. Users send from record UI (email UiType, E-maile widget, related-list envelope, history reply).

## UI flow

- Links use `Module::getComposeUrl()` → `Mail&view=Compose&sourceModule=…&sourceRecord=…` (+ optional `to`, `recordModule`, `recordId`).
- `.sendMailBtn` click → `Vtiger_Index_Js.openComposeModal()` → `triggerSendEmailModal({ view: 'IndividualSendMailModal', … })`.
- Template preview / send: `Base\Actions\Mail` modes `previewMail` / `sendMails` → `Outbound::sendFromTemplateParams` (not `Mail\Actions\Send` — full-page compose). Pass **`senderRef`** from `SenderPicker` (`account:N`). Preview has no `mailMessageId` — LinkAction vars stay deferred; send re-parses via `Outbound::sendFromTemplate` — see `link-action.mdc`.
- **Send errors (JS):** `AppConnector` resolves `{success:false, error}` in `.then()`, not `.fail()`. `registerSendMailModalView` must show `response.error.message` (server translates `LBL_*` for AJAX); do not rely on `app.vtranslate('LBL_MAIL_…')` client-side.
- **Compose senders (manual):** `Account::getComposeSenders($userId)` → at most two options: personal mailbox + one group-linked shared account (`u_yf_mail_accounts.group_id` → `vtiger_groups`). Passed as `data-mail-compose-senders` on the modal form; `SenderPicker.js` uses `config.composeSenders` (flat list, no system SMTP). Default: personal first (`defaultSenderRefForTemplate` → `getComposeSenders()[0]`). Candidates / ProjektyRekrutacyjne templates: `sender_type=user_account` (not `any` + `smtp_id`).
- **SenderPicker labels:** display `from_name <username>` (same as system SMTP rows); group uses `group_name` when `from_name` empty. `LBL_SENDER_PERSONAL` / `LBL_SENDER_GROUP` only as last-resort fallback — keys live in `Vtiger.json` `jsLanguageStrings` (not `Mail.json` alone).

## Query pitfall

`SendMailModal::getQuery()` and `Base\Actions\Mail::getQuery()` must use `RelationListView` **only when** `sourceModule !== $moduleName`.

Same-module detail compose (e.g. Candidates → Candidates) → `ListView` + `selected_ids`. Cross-module (Projekt parent → Candidates related row) → `RelationListView`.

Passing `sourceModule === moduleName` triggers `>>> No relationModel instance, requires verification 1 <<<`.

## URL params

| Param | Role |
|-------|------|
| `sourceModule` / `sourceRecord` | TextParser `$(sourceRecord:…)` context (often parent project) |
| `recordModule` / `recordId` | Recipient record when different from source (related list) |
| `to` | Pre-select email field in `IndividualSendMailModal` |

## Still full-page / legacy

- `Mail&view=Compose` — PDF redirect, direct links; no live template preview in UI.
- List mass email — **`SendMailModal`** (same `registerSendMailModalView` + `SenderPicker` + `MailComposeAttachments` as individual modal; posts `senderRef` + `attachmentTokens`). Candidates toolbar — `showModal` + `IndividualSendMailModal` URL directly.

## IndividualSendMailModal JS (single path)

- All preview/send wiring lives in `Vtiger_Index_Js.registerSendMailModalView()`; called from `triggerSendEmailModal` and from `app.registerModal` when the loaded modal contains `.js-mail-preview-section`.
- **No inline `<script>` in `IndividualSendMailModal.tpl`** — duplicate handlers caused double `previewMail` requests and template preview races.
- Template passes context via `data-mail-*` on `.js-mail-preview-section` (raw `Json::encode`, never `toSafeHTML` on JSON — breaks `selected_ids`).
- Preview uses a request sequence counter; stale responses are ignored. Re-bind with namespaced events (`.mailPreview`, `.mailSend`).
- **Scroll chain:** `registerMailComposeScrollChain()` (same file) — wheel on modal (capture, `passive: false`): scroll **down** = `.modal-body` first, then `.js-mail-content`; scroll **up** = content first, then body. Only when `.js-mail-preview-section` is visible and content overflows. Skips `.select2-*` and PerfectScrollbar rails; call `modalBody.data('ps').update()` after body scroll.
- **Attachments:** `Mail_ComposeAttachments_Js` + partial `Base/partials/MailComposeAttachments.tpl`. Staged upload via `Mail&action=UploadComposeAttachment`; send passes `attachmentTokens` JSON to `Base\Actions\Mail::sendMails`. Staging: `cache/mail-compose/{userId}/`; cron `LBL_MAIL_COMPOSE_STAGING_CLEANUP`. **Mass send:** resolve tokens once; `Mail::sendMails` deletes staging **once after the loop** (not `composeAttachmentTokens` per row — early delete broke multi-recipient + cron attach).
- **Template standard attachments (admin):** configure on **EmailTemplates Edit** — panel `LBL_STANDARD_ATTACHMENTS` links Documents via `u_yf_documents_emailtemplates` (`EmailTemplates\Models\TemplateAttachment`). Junction columns via `Relation::getReferenceTableInfo('EmailTemplates','Documents')`: **`crmid` = Document**, **`relcrmid` = EmailTemplate**. Ajax: `EmailTemplates&action=TemplateAttachment` modes `list`/`link`/`unlink`. Upload (`Documents/MassAdd` + `TemplateAttachment::link`) or popup select; Detail Documents tab also ADD+SELECT. On compose send, linked Documents auto-attach (locked chips); resolve path `Mail::getTemplete` → `Outbound::sendFromTemplate` → `Attachment::resolveForSend` → `Mail::getAttachmentsFromDocument`.
- **Recruitment account-tier templates:** `IndividualSendMailModal` filters `ProjektyRekrutacyjne` templates by project `kontrahent` when `sourceModule=ProjektyRekrutacyjne` + `sourceRecord`. Template **Kontrahent** (`account_id`, uitype 306 MultiReference) on EmailTemplates Edit — visible when **Moduł** = `ProjektyRekrutacyjne`. See `recruitment-settings.mdc`.
- **Template attachment pitfalls:** `Relation::deleteRelation` / `Documents::unlinkRelationship` do **not** remove junction rows — **`TemplateAttachment::unlink` deletes `u_yf_documents_emailtemplates` directly**. Link/unlink call `clearCaches` on `MailAttachmentsFromTemplete` / `MailAttachmentsFromDocument`. Document bytes come from **`vtiger_notes.storage_path`** (`location_type=internal`) or `external_url` — see `documents-storage.mdc`. **`getAttachmentsFromDocument` skips files where `realpath` fails** (silent empty attach) — `link()` requires physical file on disk; send blocked via `assertAllFilesPresent` + compose UI (`hasFile` on `templateAttachments`, send button disabled). Legacy `storage/oss_mailscanner/` docs often have DB metadata but no blob. List query uses `vtiger_notes.title`.

## Attachment UI (frontend)

Bootstrap 3 for look/layout; tiny custom CSS only where BS3 lacks utilities.

- **Markup:** `btn-toolbar` + `btn-group` chips (`btn btn-default btn-xs`); add button in last `btn-group`. Template block: `p.small.text-muted` + separate `btn-toolbar`. Partial included below body in `IndividualSendMailModal.tpl`, end of form in `SendMailModal.tpl`.
- **JS:** chips inserted with `addWrap.before()` before `.js-mail-attachment-add-wrap`. Modal-wide file drop toggles `.js-mail-attachment-toolbar--drag` on the toolbar. `ResetComposeAttachment` on init + modal `hidden.bs.modal` (orphan staging caused false `LBL_MAIL_ATTACHMENT_MAX_FILES`). Uploads chained sequentially (`uploadOne` per file).
- **Custom CSS** (`ComposeAttachments.css`): filename ellipsis (`js-mail-attachment-chip-name`), upload spin, drag highlight — not button styling. Minify after edits (`frontend-assets.mdc`).

## Attachment staging permissions

PHP-FPM runs as `www-data`. `cache/mail-compose/` must be writable by `www-data` (user subdirs created on upload).

- `docker compose exec app` defaults to **root** — `mkdir cache/mail-compose` as root → `root:root` `755` → `www-data` cannot `mkdir` inside → `LBL_MAIL_ATTACHMENT_UPLOAD_FAILED` (log: `mkdir(): Permission denied` in `ComposeAttachment.php`).
- Entrypoint pre-creates `cache/mail-compose` with `www-data` ownership on `app` start; dirs created later as root still need a one-time fix.
- Fix: `docker compose exec -T -u root app chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html/cache/mail-compose` (or delete dir + restart `app`).
- `move_uploaded_file` failures log `tmp`, `dest`, `is_uploaded` to `system.log` under category `Mail`.

## Attachment persistence (after send)

- On send, staged files copy to **`storage/Mail/{Y/m}/{accountId}/{messageId}/`** + `u_yf_mail_attachments` (`Attachment::storeFromPaths`). **`Outbound::enqueue` must queue `Attachment::pathMapForSend($messageId)`** — queue rows with staging paths lose attachments when staging is cleared before cron (~1 min).
- Individual modal: `sendFromTemplate` still deletes compose tokens after one send (storage copy already enqueued). See `mail-module.mdc` outbound section.
- Paths: `ROOT_DIRECTORY` has no trailing slash — use `DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR` before `storage/`. `storage/Mail/` not in git; entrypoint creates it. Root-owned dirs → `mkdir(): Permission denied` (see `docker-commands.mdc`).

## system.log noise

- `App\Log\FileTarget` dumps `$_GET`/`$_POST` on each export. Mail body fields (`content`, `contentOverride`, `body*`, …) are **masked** as `*** (N chars)` — do not log full HTML there.
